message.content:
1. There were ten patients involved in the study.
2. The patients were randomized into two groups.
3. One group underwent aquatic physiotherapy.
4. The other group underwent conventional physiotherapy.
5. The mean age of the aquatic physiotherapy group was 42 years.
6. The age range of the aquatic physiotherapy group was 25 to 67 years.
7. The mean age of the conventional physiotherapy group was 49 years.
8. The age range of the conventional physiotherapy group was 43 to 59 years.

messages.content:
Statement: Ten patients were randomized into two groups: aquatic physiotherapy with a mean age of 42 years (range: 25–67) and conventional physiotherapy with a mean age of 49 years (range: 43–59).
